<item>
            <title>[SPARK-12102] Cast a non-nullable struct field to a nullable field during analysis</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12102</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you try &lt;tt&gt;sqlContext.sql(&quot;select case when 1&amp;gt;0 then struct(1, 2, 3, cast(hash(4) as int)) else struct(1, 2, 3, 4) end&quot;).printSchema&lt;/tt&gt;, you will see &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.spark.sql.AnalysisException: cannot resolve &apos;CASE WHEN (1 &amp;gt; 0) THEN struct(1,2,3,cast(HiveGenericUDF#org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.udf.generic.GenericUDFHash(4) as int)) ELSE struct(1,2,3,4)&apos; due to data type mismatch: THEN and ELSE expressions should all be same type or coercible to a common type; line 1 pos 85&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the nullability difference between &lt;tt&gt;4&lt;/tt&gt; (non-nullable) and &lt;tt&gt;hash(4)&lt;/tt&gt; (nullable).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems it makes sense to cast the nullability in the analysis. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
